Author-Name:   Holbrook, Morris B
Author-Name:  Schindler, Robert M
Title: 
 Some Exploratory Findings on the Development of Musical Tastes.

Journal: Journal of Consumer Research
Pages: 119-24
Issue: 1
Volume: 16
Year: 1989
Month:  June 
Abstract:

 Preferences toward popular music appear to reflect tastes acquired during
 late adolescence or early adulthood. In an empirical investigation of this
 parsimonious inductive proposition, both the aggregate results (R = 0.84)
 and the disaggregated findings (R = 0.46) suggest that the development of
 tastes for popular music follows an inverted U-shaped pattern that reaches
 a peak in about the 24th year. Possible explanations include intrinsic
 components (e.g., a developmental period of maximum sensitivity analogous
 to the critical periods documented in ethological studies of imprinting)
 and extrinsic components (e.g., social pressures from one's peer group
 that reach peak intensity during a particular phase in one's life cycle.)

