Title: 
 On the Use of Component Scores in the Presence of Group Structure.

Journal: Journal of Consumer Research
Pages: 106-12
Issue: 1
Volume: 16
Year: 1989
Month:  June 
Abstract:

 Examination of the properties of component scores in the presence of
 group structure shows that the first few components extracted, typically
 viewed as most informative regarding total variance, do not necessarily
 contain the most information across group differences.  A method for
 identifying informative components that account for across group
 differences is presented and illustrated.


